<br>
Gnome pros.<br>
<br>
- They finally gave them cultural, not sure how good the stuff it however<br>
<br>
- They have the third highest starting int.<br>
<br>
- They are not as hated as a Iksar or Dark Elf.<br>
<br>
- They can tinker.<br>
<br>
Gnome cons.<br>
<br>
- They don't have the regen of an Iksar.<br>
<br>
- They don't have the high int of an Erudite.<br>
<br>
- I think their newbie area sucks.<br>
<br>
- No enhanced regen with out AA's.<br>
<br>
Human Pros.<br>
<br>
- They aren't as hated as Dark Elves and Iksar.<br>
<br>
Human Cons.<br>
<br>
- They have only average stats.<br>
<br>
- Can't see squat in the dark with out sight enhancing spells.<br>
<br>
- No enhanced regen without AA's.<br>
<br>
Iksar Pros.<br>
<br>
- They have best regen out of races that can practice necromancy.<br>
<br>
- Field of Bone is a very nice newbie zone. (Bone chips anyone?)<br>
<br>
<br>
Iksar Cons.<br>
<br>
- They have no cultural armor that I'm aware of.<br>
<br>
- They are even more hated then human, gnome and erudite necromancers.<br>
<br>
- Tied for lowest starting int with humans.<br>
<br>
- Xp penalty.<br>
<br>
Dark Elf Pros.<br>
<br>
- Second only to Erudites in starting int.<br>
<br>
- Has cultural armor.<br>
<br>
- Can see in the dark.<br>
<br>
Dark Elf Cons.<br>
<br>
- Only race of necros hated more are Iksar.<br>
<br>
- Nektulos sucks for newbie area.<br>
<br>
- No enhanced regen with out AA's.<br>
<br>
Erudite Pros.<br>
<br>
- Highest starting int which allows you to switch out int for hp gear earlier.<br>
<br>
- Very nice Cultural armors available to them.<br>
<br>
- Paineel newbie zone is very good until level 4.<br>
<br>
- Not as hated as Iksar and Dark Elves.<br>
<br>
Erudite Cons.<br>
<br>
- Very low str so will need + str items to make for easier farming.<br>
<br>
- Blind as a bat in the dark, need sight enhancing spells.<br>
<br>
- No enhanced regen with out AA's.<br>
<br>
I'm sure I have forgotten a few points but I would urge you inf to check the necro site I have in our links section. Necros there that have played since before kunark and they know their shit. Tons of good info and guides there.<br>
<br>
